02:15:06.58 --> 02:15:07.42
Who was cool about that?

2905
02:15:07.42 --> 02:15:09.38
The gunners on the ground.

2906
02:15:09.38 --> 02:15:10.34
The enemy gunners?

2907
02:15:10.34 --> 02:15:11.18
Yeah.

2908
02:15:11.18 --> 02:15:12.02
In what way?

2909
02:15:12.02 --> 02:15:13.90
Well, they'd know you were there,

2910
02:15:13.90 --> 02:15:15.30
because they could hear you.

2911
02:15:15.30 --> 02:15:20.30
And in your orbiting,

2912
02:15:20.30 --> 02:15:21.86
what I would do immediately,

2913
02:15:21.86 --> 02:15:23.30
as soon as we get there,

2914
02:15:23.30 --> 02:15:25.42
I'd separate an altitude,

2915
02:15:25.42 --> 02:15:29.06
I'd go a thousand higher on whoever was,

2916
02:15:29.06 --> 02:15:30.78
usually a rural gardener,

2917
02:15:30.78 --> 02:15:32.62
but I'd go a thousand higher,

2918
02:15:32.62 --> 02:15:34.94
and I'd cut across and turn,

2919
02:15:34.94 --> 02:15:38.78
every naval aviator is a left-hand turn expert.

2920
02:15:38.78 --> 02:15:39.66
They're all turned left.

2921
02:15:39.66 --> 02:15:42.42
In fact, one time I met a guy in Philadelphia

2922
02:15:42.42 --> 02:15:43.82
who had the same dog as I did,

2923
02:15:43.82 --> 02:15:44.94
and I started talking with him,

2924
02:15:44.94 --> 02:15:47.18
