02:16:46.50 --> 02:16:47.34
Cool.

2950
02:16:47.34 --> 02:16:49.74
You make yourself present,

2951
02:16:49.74 --> 02:16:52.42
because you're making all that noise right over here,

2952
02:16:52.42 --> 02:16:53.58
over the crossroads,

2953
02:16:53.58 --> 02:16:55.22
and they know, the gunners all know,

2954
02:16:55.22 --> 02:16:57.02
as the trucks are over there,

2955
02:16:57.02 --> 02:16:57.86
and they know that,

2956
02:16:57.86 --> 02:16:59.70
and they know that you know that,

2957
02:16:59.70 --> 02:17:02.34
because they can hear the fact flying around too.

2958
02:17:02.34 --> 02:17:06.90
So they would wait until you roll in, until you commit.

2959
02:17:06.90 --> 02:17:09.66
The problem is, they had to get a handle on you

2960
02:17:09.66 --> 02:17:10.66
when you start down,

2961
02:17:10.66 --> 02:17:14.38
because they also know, I presume that they knew,

2962
02:17:14.38 --> 02:17:15.70
that you're gonna pull a powered idle,

2963
02:17:15.70 --> 02:17:17.30
and your engines get very quiet,

2964
02:17:17.30 --> 02:17:19.34
as soon as you do that.

2965
02:17:19.34 --> 02:17:22.86
So if they didn't have a bead on you, at that point,

2966
02:17:22.86 --> 02:17:24.10
I'm convinced too,

2967
02:17:24.10 --> 02:17:29.10
that they used a simple auditory way to track you.

2968
02:17:31.82 --> 02:17:35.38
I think my idea is that,

2969
02:17:35.38 --> 02:17:38.78
if you took a bunch of paper towel tubes,

2970
02:17:38.78 --> 02:17:40.18
and put tape around them,

2971
02:17:40.18 --> 02:17:42.58
and put a microphone behind them,

2972
02:17:42.58 --> 02:17:47.26
and then you put that on the mount of a gun,

2973
02:17:47.26 --> 02:17:49.98
where the barrel got overheated and it warped,

2974
02:17:49.98 --> 02:17:54.38
so we got this gun mount over here, we don't use it,

2975
02:17:54.38 --> 02:17:59.38
put that auditory search finder thing on the gun,

2976
02:18:00.10 --> 02:18:02.06
because as soon as I turn it over there,

2977
02:18:02.06 --> 02:18:02.90
and I can hear it,

2978
02:18:02.90 --> 02:18:04.62
I got headphones on, and I can hear,

2979
02:18:04.62 --> 02:18:08.06
there he is, oh, I lost him, no, I got him back again.

2980
02:18:08.06 --> 02:18:09.66
But the point here is that,

2981
02:18:09.66 --> 02:18:13.70
the azimuth and elevation on that auditory device,

2982
02:18:13.70 --> 02:18:15.54
if you have a simple system,

2983
02:18:15.54 --> 02:18:19.82
you can all the five guys having 57 millimeter,

2984
02:18:19.82 --> 02:18:22.18
or even 85 millimeter pieces around here,

2985
02:18:22.18 --> 02:18:23.82
they know where you are,

2986
02:18:23.82 --> 02:18:27.38
because they can read what he is tracking you

2987
02:18:27.38 --> 02:18:29.54
in an auditory fashion.

2988
02:18:29.54 --> 02:18:33.14
So they wouldn't open up sometimes,

2989
02:18:33.14 --> 02:18:36.46
until you release,

2990
02:18:36.46 --> 02:18:40.46
pull, and add power, and as soon as you did that,

2991
02:18:41.70 --> 02:18:46.10
yeah, that's shit going by from the back,

2992
02:18:46.10 --> 02:18:49.26
and most of it right there,

2993
02:18:49.26 --> 02:18:52.26
because they had time to know where you were,

2994
02:18:52.26 --> 02:18:54.62
and they could hear you in orbit,

2995
02:18:54.62 --> 02:18:56.90
and now this guy was over here,

