How's this wearing on you mentally?

3058
02:21:53.34 --> 02:21:56.94
Not bad, I think at that age, you're in your late 20s,

3059
02:21:56.94 --> 02:21:59.46
I was in my late 20s, no, not a big deal,

3060
02:21:59.46 --> 02:22:03.78
except that air conditioning on some ships

3061
02:22:03.78 --> 02:22:06.10
was not very good, and Constellation was one of them,

3062
02:22:06.10 --> 02:22:08.62
the flight tag, or the O3 level.

3063
02:22:08.62 --> 02:22:10.10
Who did it to a Navy guy,

3064
02:22:10.10 --> 02:22:12.14
where that air conditioning pisses us off

3065
02:22:12.14 --> 02:22:13.22
all the time on a ship?

3066
02:22:13.22 --> 02:22:15.58
Well, how about you just had good ventilation,

3067
02:22:15.58 --> 02:22:20.46
you know, you have 85 degree air outside,

3068
02:22:20.46 --> 02:22:22.66
put 85 degree air in this room.

3069
02:22:22.66 --> 02:22:24.10
That would be nice.

3070
02:22:24.10 --> 02:22:29.70
You know, and my state room was on the O3 level,

3071
02:22:29.70 --> 02:22:33.10
the O4 level is the flight, yeah.

3072
02:22:33.10 --> 02:22:35.66
So there are places in the ship

3073
02:22:35.66 --> 02:22:38.78
where the air conditioning really did work beautifully,

3074
02:22:38.78 --> 02:22:44.58
but we got visited by ABC or CBS News or something like that,

3075
02:22:44.58 --> 02:22:45.70
and they were on Hancock,

3076
02:22:45.70 --> 02:22:48.86
which was in the Gulf at the same time at that time,

3077
02:22:48.86 --> 02:22:50.46
and one of these guys said to me,

3078
02:22:50.46 --> 02:22:53.22
boy, we could see this ship on the horizon,

3079
02:22:53.22 --> 02:22:56.50
and he said, this ship is nice, Hancock,

3080
02:22:56.50 --> 02:23:01.34
but next week we're going down to get aboard the big guy.

3081
02:23:01.34 --> 02:23:02.82
Air conditioning doesn't work here,

3082
02:23:02.82 --> 02:23:05.86
and the food's not real good.

3083
02:23:05.86 --> 02:23:07.78
Better on a Hancock than everywhere.

3084
02:23:07.78 --> 02:23:10.70
I said, well, fortunes of war, I guess.

3085
02:23:10.70 --> 02:23:13.50
Yeah, I had a guy on the podcast named Dean Ladd,

3086
02:23:13.50 --> 02:23:14.98
who's a Marine in World War II,

3087
02:23:14.98 --> 02:23:17.06
and he went into a bunch of different islands,

3088
02:23:17.06 --> 02:23:21.06
but he was talking, he's going into Tarawa,

3089
02:23:21.06 --> 02:23:23.42
and I'm like, were you nervous going in?

3090
02:23:23.42 --> 02:23:25.06
He said, no, it's the other guys

3091
02:23:25.06 --> 02:23:27.02
that are going to get wounded and killed.

3092
02:23:27.02 --> 02:23:29.30
He ended up getting gut shot in Tarawa,

3093
02:23:29.30 --> 02:23:32.78
and was lucky, a couple of his Marines disobeyed the order

3094
02:23:32.78 --> 02:23:33.66
just to keep going,

3095
02:23:33.66 --> 02:23:35.26
and they grabbed him and threw him back on a ship,

3096
02:23:35.26 --> 02:23:39.30
so I think that's the common mental state

3097
02:23:39.30 --> 02:23:42.58
of the young man in combat is I really feel sorry

3098
02:23:42.58 --> 02:23:45.10
for the other guys that are going to have trouble out here

3099
02:23:45.10 --> 02:23:46.46
and get wounded and killed.

3100
02:23:46.46 --> 02:23:48.18
My favorite professor in college,

3101
02:23:48.18 --> 02:23:51.30
University of Chicago PhD, that's a big deal,

3102
02:23:51.30 --> 02:23:56.30
and Econ was a tail gunner in B-17s in World War II,

3103
02:23:57.14 --> 02:23:58.70
and I used to play chess with him,

3104
02:23:58.70 --> 02:24:01.26
and I said to him, what was it like?

3105
02:24:01.26 --> 02:24:03.98
He said, you always figured the other guy's going to get it.

3106
02:24:03.98 --> 02:24:06.98
That's the same thing I would just say.

3107
02:24:06.98 --> 02:24:09.98
That's a pretty impressive statement for a tail gunner,

3108
02:24:09.98 --> 02:24:11.90
B-17 in World War II.

3109
02:24:11.90 --> 02:24:14.62
He was a teenager, yeah, and he said,

3110
02:24:14.62 --> 02:24:16.74
you always, fortunes of war,

3111
02:24:16.74 --> 02:24:18.70
you figured the other guy's going to,

3112
02:24:18.70 --> 02:24:20.90
or you can always jump out, you know.

3113
02:24:20.90 --> 02:24:23.66
Yeah, that's one.

3114
02:24:23.66 --> 02:24:26.22
That would be the worst of it that you had to bail out.

3115
02:24:26.22 --> 02:24:28.34
Any other highlights from that deployment?

3116
02:24:30.70 --> 02:24:34.78
Well, like, as Skepper said to me,

3117
02:24:34.78 --> 02:24:37.82
we want to send somebody over to Thailand,

3118
02:24:37.82 --> 02:24:40.50
and since you have Air Force experience,

3119
02:24:40.50 --> 02:24:42.46
would you like to do it?

3120
02:24:42.46 --> 02:24:43.74
Well, yeah, why not?

3121
02:24:43.74 --> 02:24:45.46
And this is to be a forward air control or something?

3122
02:24:45.46 --> 02:24:50.46
No, just to make some judgments

3123
02:24:50.46 --> 02:24:54.38
and come back and relate how they do things over there

3124
02:24:54.38 --> 02:24:57.10
and how the facts work and stuff like that.

3125
02:24:57.10 --> 02:24:59.78
So I said, okay, and so they took me over in a cod,

3126
02:24:59.78 --> 02:25:02.98
and we did not get shot at in broad daylight.

3127
02:25:02.98 --> 02:25:04.50
Cod went out in daylight,

3128
02:25:04.50 --> 02:25:08.62
and we didn't get shot at crossing or anything out

3129
02:25:08.62 --> 02:25:11.06
into U-Bahn is where I went,

3130
02:25:11.06 --> 02:25:16.06
where Robin Oles was when he made his five kills

3131
02:25:16.66 --> 02:25:18.22
and stuff like that.

3132
02:25:18.22 --> 02:25:22.66
And initially, hard to get to first base there.

3133
02:25:22.66 --> 02:25:25.10
I said, it was like in the movies.

3134
02:25:25.10 --> 02:25:29.14
The cod pulled out onto the grass,

3135
02:25:29.14 --> 02:25:31.78
and the crewmen opened the back door and they hopped out.

3136
02:25:31.78 --> 02:25:36.78
They had shut down the starboard engine and door slammed.

3137
02:25:37.06 --> 02:25:39.54
Starboard engine started up, taxied away.

3138
02:25:39.54 --> 02:25:43.70
It was standing there with my suitcase on the grass.

3139
02:25:43.70 --> 02:25:48.70
This is just like a goofy movie from France

3140
02:25:49.90 --> 02:25:52.26
and World War II or something anyway.

3141
02:25:52.26 --> 02:25:57.26
So I got a guy, a trooper walking down the tarmac somewhere,

3142
02:25:57.90 --> 02:26:00.30
and I said, where's Base Operations?

3143
02:26:00.30 --> 02:26:02.38
Down the street, but you don't wanna go there.

3144
02:26:02.38 --> 02:26:03.26
Why?

3145
02:26:03.26 --> 02:26:06.06
Because we're not allowed to be here.

3146
02:26:06.06 --> 02:26:07.50
We're guests.

3147
02:26:07.50 --> 02:26:09.86
Oh, where do I go?

3148
02:26:09.86 --> 02:26:13.34
Building 386, it's on the second street over

3149
02:26:13.34 --> 02:26:15.98
and it has 386 on the outside.

3150
02:26:15.98 --> 02:26:17.38
And I'm making this part up,

3151
02:26:17.38 --> 02:26:19.70
but there's a bit in the essence of it.

3152
02:26:19.70 --> 02:26:22.82
That's the operations you want.

3153
02:26:22.82 --> 02:26:26.22
So I didn't have a place to sleep or anything.

3154
02:26:26.22 --> 02:26:30.70
I went there and it got a Marine, no,

3155
02:26:30.70 --> 02:26:35.38
Air Force Trooper, big guy, big guy with a sidearm

3156
02:26:35.38 --> 02:26:39.18
at a little lectern inside the door.

3157
02:26:39.18 --> 02:26:41.78
He said, basically he says, who the hell are you?

3158
02:26:41.78 --> 02:26:44.78
I mean, maybe uniform and whatnot.

3159
02:26:44.78 --> 02:26:48.70
And he said, not without whatever he needed.

3160
02:26:50.34 --> 02:26:52.98
So that night I went to the club

3161
02:26:52.98 --> 02:26:55.98
and I meet a guy, an Air Force major,

3162
02:26:55.98 --> 02:26:57.62
and he said, we can take care of you.

3163
02:26:57.62 --> 02:26:59.02
We'll get past that, don't worry about it.

3164
02:26:59.02 --> 02:27:02.38
And he took care of everything and stuff like that.

3165
02:27:02.38 --> 02:27:07.38
But Air Force operations were officially just a guest

3166
02:27:07.38 --> 02:27:09.10
and they were just don't officially,

3167
02:27:09.10 --> 02:27:13.90
the air force, the tarmac loaded with F-4s and C-130s.

3168
02:27:13.90 --> 02:27:17.94
So I got to fly with a guy who flew the OV-10,

3169
02:27:17.94 --> 02:27:20.46
which is a heck of a fun airplane to fly.

3170
02:27:20.46 --> 02:27:24.10
Man, oh man, I'd swap ends in a second with that thing.

3171
02:27:24.10 --> 02:27:27.10
I mean, this way and that sort of thing.

3172
02:27:27.10 --> 02:27:30.18
Tons of power, two turboprop engines

3173
02:27:30.18 --> 02:27:32.54
and designed for the Marines.

3174
02:27:32.54 --> 02:27:35.54
So you could put one in it, a couple of guys in the back

3175
02:27:35.54 --> 02:27:37.34
and they opened the hatch in the back

3176
02:27:37.34 --> 02:27:41.86
and the Marines can parachute out into middle of nowhere

3177
02:27:41.86 --> 02:27:43.58
and stuff like that.

3178
02:27:43.58 --> 02:27:47.46
And a good panel in the bay made an instrument approach

3179
02:27:47.46 --> 02:27:50.14
with that guy and he said, that's really something

3180
02:27:50.14 --> 02:27:51.94
off that terrible panel back there.

3181
02:27:51.94 --> 02:27:55.18
I said, yeah, well, you make about 100 passes at the ship

3182
02:27:55.18 --> 02:27:57.98
and then at night and it's not a big deal anymore.

3183
02:27:57.98 --> 02:28:02.98
Now, I flew with him maybe twice

3184
02:28:03.74 --> 02:28:06.74
and I flew with the C-130 gunship,

3185
02:28:06.74 --> 02:28:10.66
a C-130 forward air controller,

3186
02:28:10.66 --> 02:28:12.22
only at night for him though,

3187
02:28:12.22 --> 02:28:13.98
because it's a big target, I guess.

3188
02:28:16.02 --> 02:28:18.50
We had flown off of that guy,

3189
02:28:18.50 --> 02:28:20.82
but we didn't know what kind of airplane he had.

3190
02:28:21.78 --> 02:28:26.78
And let's see, the OV-10 and two times with the C-130,

3191
02:28:26.78 --> 02:28:29.34
two times with the C-130, there's only there a week.

3192
02:28:30.34 --> 02:28:34.46
And then back out to the ship,

3193
02:28:38.42 --> 02:28:43.42
C-130, no, C-47 had about eight or 10 Marine troopers

3194
02:28:48.66 --> 02:28:52.66
who were there on R&R at Yubon, Thailand.

3195
02:28:52.66 --> 02:28:55.18
They had been downtown and they all looked at it.

3196
02:28:55.18 --> 02:28:59.10
They were like, oh, they're the big night last night.

3197
02:29:00.02 --> 02:29:01.58
I don't know where they wound up going,

3198
02:29:01.58 --> 02:29:03.50
but they dropped me off at Hway,

3199
02:29:03.50 --> 02:29:06.10
it was right after the battle of Hway,

3200
02:29:06.10 --> 02:29:08.14
they destroyed everything.

3201
02:29:08.14 --> 02:29:12.62
And right next to the runway, Matt runway,

3202
02:29:12.62 --> 02:29:15.10
and when we landed on that, Matt runway,

3203
02:29:15.10 --> 02:29:15.98
they're shooting at us,

3204
02:29:15.98 --> 02:29:17.78
because it goes rattle, rattle, rattle,

3205
02:29:17.78 --> 02:29:20.58
and I thought, oh my God, there's something.

3206
02:29:20.58 --> 02:29:24.34
But that's, it was just a plank runway.

3207
02:29:24.34 --> 02:29:25.66
And then the Army was there.

3208
02:29:25.66 --> 02:29:30.66
And I thought, boy, sandbags and logs and mud,

3209
02:29:30.66 --> 02:29:33.82
and oh, thank heaven, I have no part of the Army.

3210
02:29:33.82 --> 02:29:36.02
And anyway, they sent the cod in there

3211
02:29:36.02 --> 02:29:39.62
and the cod picked me up and took me out to the ship.

3212
02:29:39.62 --> 02:29:41.50
So that was the end of that.

3213
02:29:41.50 --> 02:29:44.10
But that was quite an experience.

3214
02:29:46.42 --> 02:29:50.14
Those C-130 guys, they had call-onness,

3215
02:29:50.14 --> 02:29:54.78
they've sacked their parachutes back over here

3216
02:29:54.78 --> 02:29:57.26
and they have a pile back there.

3217
02:29:57.26 --> 02:29:58.94
Really?

3218
02:29:58.94 --> 02:30:00.38
What do you do if you get hit?

3219
02:30:00.38 --> 02:30:02.70
Because in my mind, you get hit,

3220
02:30:02.70 --> 02:30:05.34
you might take the whole wing off or the end of it

3221
02:30:05.34 --> 02:30:06.78
and then it starts to tumble

3222
02:30:06.78 --> 02:30:10.14
and you're not gonna have time to put on a parachute.

3223
02:30:10.14 --> 02:30:13.18
But they did, I think they lost more C-130s

3224
02:30:13.18 --> 02:30:16.90
than they ever admitted to over there.

3225
02:30:16.90 --> 02:30:21.58
Because the one I was on, the gunship, he's at 3,000 feet

3226
02:30:21.58 --> 02:30:26.14
and the 37 millimeter gets to 3,000 feet.

3227
02:30:26.14 --> 02:30:28.06
And the burst went off in front of the nose

3228
02:30:28.06 --> 02:30:31.62
and I hit the deck behind the naval flight deck

3229
02:30:31.62 --> 02:30:33.10
on that airplane.

3230
02:30:33.10 --> 02:30:37.26
I was on the floor as we flew through the smoke.

3231
02:30:37.26 --> 02:30:40.14
And they said, what was that?

3232
02:30:40.14 --> 02:30:41.74
I said, for heaven's sake, it went off right.

3233
02:30:41.74 --> 02:30:44.78
Yeah, but it falls away, don't worry about it.

3234
02:30:44.78 --> 02:30:46.54
All right?

3235
02:30:46.54 --> 02:30:47.98
But we flew through the smoke.

3236
02:30:47.98 --> 02:30:50.42
I saw the smoke go over the windshield.

3237
02:30:51.62 --> 02:30:53.54
And I got the flight C-130 a little bit,

3238
02:30:53.54 --> 02:30:56.50
just steer it around, not a big deal.

3239
02:30:56.50 --> 02:30:58.82
But anyway, that's what I did in Thailand.

3240
02:30:58.82 --> 02:31:00.50
Then I came back to the ship and I said,

3241
02:31:00.50 --> 02:31:01.74
what about this and what about that?

3242
02:31:01.74 --> 02:31:06.26
And that's when I saw those F-4s making multiple passes

3243
02:31:06.26 --> 02:31:10.22
from the same direction at 30 degrees dive

3244
02:31:11.46 --> 02:31:14.94
and not just the same direction,

3245
02:31:14.94 --> 02:31:17.78
but both airplanes from the same direction.

3246
02:31:19.78 --> 02:31:23.70
Maybe you're losing airplanes and I think I know why.

3247
02:31:23.70 --> 02:31:25.62
No talking them out of it.

3248
02:31:25.62 --> 02:31:28.78
I think if you are encouraged to think

3249
02:31:28.78 --> 02:31:32.58
that 60 degree angle of dive is dangerous, you'll believe it.

3250
02:31:34.70 --> 02:31:36.58
But it's not, it's safer.

3251
02:31:36.58 --> 02:31:37.82
It's a better way to go.

3252
02:31:37.82 --> 02:31:39.14
And when I saw that picture,

3253
02:31:40.14 --> 02:31:43.02
I don't know if I said this now,

3254
02:31:43.02 --> 02:31:46.02
there's a famous picture taken during the Battle of Midway.

3255
02:31:46.02 --> 02:31:49.42
And that guy is virtually 89 degrees

3256
02:31:50.30 --> 02:31:52.02
all above a Japanese carrier.

3257
02:31:53.34 --> 02:31:55.66
So that's the way to do it, I thought.

3258
02:31:55.66 --> 02:31:57.78
And besides, gotta get the barrel all the way up there.

3259
02:31:57.78 --> 02:31:58.78
Maybe he can't do that.

3260
02:32:01.46 --> 02:32:04.22
So you get done with that deployment.

3261
02:32:05.74 --> 02:32:08.46
Head back to the States, now it's what, 1970?

3262
02:32:10.74 --> 02:32:11.58
Yeah.

3263
02:32:11.58 --> 02:32:13.74
And you're coming back to America now,

3264
02:32:13.74 --> 02:32:17.54
now you got the protests and all this stuff going on.

3265
02:32:17.54 --> 02:32:19.58
Where's that, are you seeing that?

3266
02:32:19.58 --> 02:32:20.86
Are you aware of that?

3267
02:32:20.86 --> 02:32:22.50
What's, how's that impacted you?

3268
02:32:22.50 --> 02:32:23.62
Very much so.

3269
02:32:23.62 --> 02:32:27.30
And I think you just get used to it.

3270
02:32:27.30 --> 02:32:29.38
The thing that you wouldn't get used to

3271
02:32:29.38 --> 02:32:31.70
if you were a newly married guy,

3272
02:32:31.70 --> 02:32:35.02
and that was me and a lot of other guys too,

3273
02:32:35.02 --> 02:32:37.18
that they would call up your house and say,

3274
02:32:37.18 --> 02:32:39.70
tell you that, tell your little wife

3275
02:32:39.70 --> 02:32:42.54
that you had been killed that night.

3276
02:32:42.54 --> 02:32:46.34
This is stateside, before you went to sea.

3277
02:32:46.34 --> 02:32:48.38
Very evil, that's evil.

3278
02:32:49.26 --> 02:32:53.02
And then of course we had a couple of bad actions.

3279
02:32:53.02 --> 02:32:56.34
There was a Navy Cod, I think an old one,

3280
02:32:56.34 --> 02:33:00.30
with a bunch of guys on board that crashed on San Clemente

3281
02:33:01.66 --> 02:33:03.94
before we sailed.

3282
02:33:03.94 --> 02:33:06.70
That was very bad and made my wife very squirrely,

3283
02:33:06.70 --> 02:33:08.50
my young wife.

3284
02:33:08.50 --> 02:33:11.14
There's a funny thing, there's a funny one here.

3285
02:33:11.14 --> 02:33:15.98
I went to the East Coast and I flew out to the East Coast

3286
02:33:15.98 --> 02:33:18.26
so then I have to ride back.

3287
02:33:18.26 --> 02:33:23.26
So we're on a DC-4, C-40, 51,

3288
02:33:24.66 --> 02:33:27.50
or God knows what, a four engine,

3289
02:33:27.50 --> 02:33:31.34
unpressurized Navy transport.

3290
02:33:31.34 --> 02:33:34.58
And we get to Houston and the guy says,

3291
02:33:34.58 --> 02:33:36.94
ah, we'll be here overnight because

3292
02:33:36.94 --> 02:33:41.94
we wasn't so on the third engine or something

3293
02:33:42.18 --> 02:33:45.14
that's not right and so be prepared.

3294
02:33:45.14 --> 02:33:47.86
We'll have it, it'll be ready by morning.

3295
02:33:47.86 --> 02:33:50.90
So at any rate, we were supposed to be back

3296
02:33:50.90 --> 02:33:53.54
at Miramar by six p.m. more or less.

3297
02:33:53.54 --> 02:33:56.34
I sent her, called her or something

3298
02:33:56.34 --> 02:33:59.06
from the East Coast from Norfolk.

3299
02:33:59.06 --> 02:34:01.38
So she calls the duty officer

3300
02:34:01.38 --> 02:34:04.50
and the Whitehead sailor who's on duty too,

3301
02:34:04.50 --> 02:34:07.50
he answers the phone and she says, is this Mrs. Coppell?

3302
02:34:07.50 --> 02:34:10.18
Is my husband gonna be there tonight?

3303
02:34:10.18 --> 02:34:12.18
Well, it's his ETA and he says,

3304
02:34:12.18 --> 02:34:14.42
oh no, the airplane went down in Houston.

