02:48:49.76 --> 02:48:54.24
And I buy the rugs for $1,500 because there's

3597
02:48:54.24 --> 02:48:59.40
certain human psychology, certain price levels in which

3598
02:48:59.40 --> 02:49:05.20
a retail customer, knowing that you could pay more,

3599
02:49:05.20 --> 02:49:08.40
but I won't do that because I don't want surprises

3600
02:49:08.40 --> 02:49:09.52
and stuff like that.

3601
02:49:09.52 --> 02:49:12.04
So you know you're going to get them for $1,500

3602
02:49:12.04 --> 02:49:12.88
if you drive all.

3603
02:49:12.88 --> 02:49:14.28
Because you talk to the auctioneer

3604
02:49:14.28 --> 02:49:16.16
and he tells you more or less what it is.

3605
02:49:16.16 --> 02:49:18.12
And he thinks he knows and stuff like that.

3606
02:49:18.12 --> 02:49:20.92
So he drives to Altoona and you look at it and say, yeah,

3607
02:49:20.92 --> 02:49:23.12
I can get $6,000 for this.

3608
02:49:23.12 --> 02:49:26.92
I won't pay more than, have to pay more than $1,500.

3609
02:49:26.92 --> 02:49:27.60
And you do that.

3610
02:49:27.60 --> 02:49:30.92
So I came back from Altoona that day to this guy's place.

3611
02:49:30.92 --> 02:49:33.48
And he's in a secondhand equipment business,

3612
02:49:33.48 --> 02:49:37.32
secondhand commercial equipment, big ovens and mixers

3613
02:49:37.32 --> 02:49:38.52
and things like that.

3614
02:49:38.52 --> 02:49:40.64
They go on forever.

3615
02:49:40.64 --> 02:49:44.52
And he said, you bake bread once in a while.

3616
02:49:44.52 --> 02:49:47.20
And I didn't buy anything that day.

3617
02:49:47.20 --> 02:49:51.64
And I had money in my pocket, cash in my pocket.

3618
02:49:51.64 --> 02:49:53.76
He sent a couple of nice ovens over here.

3619
02:49:53.76 --> 02:49:56.48
I said, I'm not interested.

3620
02:49:56.48 --> 02:49:57.80
He said, look at them.

3621
02:49:57.80 --> 02:49:58.36
They're diner size.

3622
02:49:58.36 --> 02:50:00.44
They're not the full size.

3623
02:50:00.44 --> 02:50:04.28
You've got to find exactly the right guy.

3624
02:50:04.28 --> 02:50:08.28
Probably a diner, but he already has.

3625
02:50:08.28 --> 02:50:12.92
I'll sell them to you for $900.

3626
02:50:12.92 --> 02:50:14.04
I don't want them.

3627
02:50:14.04 --> 02:50:16.44
He said, I can slide them right onto your truck.

3628
02:50:16.44 --> 02:50:20.16
And he didn't know I had money in my pocket either.

3629
02:50:20.16 --> 02:50:21.16
Yeah, he did.

3630
02:50:21.16 --> 02:50:24.08
Yeah, maybe.

3631
02:50:24.08 --> 02:50:27.44
So finally I said, OK.

3632
02:50:27.44 --> 02:50:30.84
So then I had to install them myself.

3633
02:50:30.84 --> 02:50:32.72
We live in an old Pennsylvania Dutch.

3634
02:50:32.72 --> 02:50:37.40
I call them a Pennsylvania German soft brick drafty.

3635
02:50:37.40 --> 02:50:39.96
And they have matching porches on both sides.

3636
02:50:39.96 --> 02:50:41.36
And this is porches in clothes.

3637
02:50:41.36 --> 02:50:45.08
So I put them on that porch and had heavy.

3638
02:50:45.08 --> 02:50:48.64
You know, they weigh, I don't know, 1,000 a piece, I guess.

3639
02:50:48.64 --> 02:50:52.24
Jacks and everything and blocks and getting it up and sliding

3640
02:50:52.24 --> 02:50:54.28
over and installing both of them.

3641
02:50:54.28 --> 02:50:58.20
But I didn't do very much until my sister-in-law actually

3642
02:50:58.20 --> 02:51:03.20
said, you need to put bread with Joe at the skip-hack.

3643
02:51:03.20 --> 02:51:04.60
Farmers market on Sunday.

3644
02:51:04.60 --> 02:51:08.12
So then one thing led to another led to another.

3645
02:51:08.12 --> 02:51:11.56
And then I went to this nice guy at Kimberton Whole Foods,

3646
02:51:11.56 --> 02:51:14.000
who was at the time he had one store.

3647
02:51:14.000 --> 02:51:16.96
And he was on the floor himself.

3648
02:51:16.96 --> 02:51:20.32
And I said, do you think he can sell these?

3649
02:51:20.32 --> 02:51:24.92
He said, probably not, because a lot of us just bailed out of here.

3650
02:51:24.92 --> 02:51:27.52
But you can put it on their shelves if you want.

3651
02:51:27.52 --> 02:51:30.84
Came back the next day and there was six of them sold.

3652
02:51:30.84 --> 02:51:32.04
I said, can I put more?

3653
02:51:32.04 --> 02:51:32.92
Of course.

3654
02:51:32.92 --> 02:51:34.16
So one thing led to another.

3655
02:51:34.16 --> 02:51:38.04
He has about, maybe he has eight stores now.

3656
02:51:38.04 --> 02:51:40.24
And I'm in four.

3657
02:51:40.24 --> 02:51:42.64
So you're making bread every day?

3658
02:51:42.64 --> 02:51:43.44
I work, no.

3659
02:51:43.44 --> 02:51:48.04
I work Tuesday, Wednesday and Thursday.

3660
02:51:48.04 --> 02:51:52.40
And I deliver on Wednesday what I made on Tuesday night

3661
02:51:52.40 --> 02:51:55.28
and sliced Wednesday morning to deliver that.

3662
02:51:55.28 --> 02:51:59.84
Then I work Thursday and deliver that on Friday.

3663
02:51:59.84 --> 02:52:03.08
And then I'm off Saturday, Sunday, Monday.

3664
02:52:03.08 --> 02:52:05.04
But I got another racket gone.

3665
02:52:05.04 --> 02:52:06.84
What's the other racket?

3666
02:52:06.84 --> 02:52:09.24
When I ran for Congress.

3667
02:52:09.24 --> 02:52:10.68
I don't know if you know I did this.

3668
02:52:10.68 --> 02:52:11.60
I did know that, yeah.

3669
02:52:11.60 --> 02:52:12.44
It was in your notes.

3670
02:52:12.44 --> 02:52:15.04
Yeah.

3671
02:52:15.04 --> 02:52:16.24
I was supposed to lose.

3672
02:52:16.24 --> 02:52:18.28
And it was in the gentlemen's agreement.

3673
02:52:18.28 --> 02:52:21.08
You want a guy who can lose gracefully.

3674
02:52:21.08 --> 02:52:23.64
And I said, that's exactly right.

3675
02:52:23.64 --> 02:52:28.48
But I thought to myself, this guy, this Congressman,

3676
02:52:28.48 --> 02:52:29.80
he drinks a lot.

3677
02:52:29.80 --> 02:52:33.72
And he may get hit by a truck or have the classic too much

3678
02:52:33.72 --> 02:52:35.84
alcohol heart attack or something like that.

3679
02:52:35.84 --> 02:52:38.80
This is the only chance I'll ever get.

3680
02:52:38.80 --> 02:52:39.76
So I did.

3681
02:52:39.76 --> 02:52:41.48
I think I put it in there.

3682
02:52:41.48 --> 02:52:43.44
I did rank 10,000 doorbells.

3683
02:52:43.44 --> 02:52:44.40
I really did.

3684
02:52:44.40 --> 02:52:45.96
It gets to be fun after a while.

3685
02:52:45.96 --> 02:52:47.56
You meet new people.

3686
02:52:47.56 --> 02:52:51.20
And moreover, they ask you questions privately

3687
02:52:51.20 --> 02:52:53.60
that you hadn't quite thought through.

3688
02:52:53.60 --> 02:52:55.72
And after you fumble around with that, you say,

3689
02:52:55.72 --> 02:52:58.60
I won't fumble around with that a second time.

3690
02:52:58.60 --> 02:53:00.64
And it turns out, two days later,

3691
02:53:00.64 --> 02:53:02.16
a guy asks you the same question.

3692
02:53:02.16 --> 02:53:02.76
I don't understand.

3693
02:53:02.76 --> 02:53:04.44
You're ready for it.

3694
02:53:04.44 --> 02:53:08.76
So after that, and he spent 10 times what I spent.

3695
02:53:08.76 --> 02:53:13.20
A US Congressman, I was told, will do anything

3696
02:53:13.20 --> 02:53:14.20
to stay in office.

3697
02:53:14.20 --> 02:53:15.64
Anything.

3698
02:53:15.64 --> 02:53:18.44
So at any rate, he spent 10 times what I had to spend.

3699
02:53:18.44 --> 02:53:20.36
I had the $35,000 to spend.

3700
02:53:20.36 --> 02:53:22.64
He spent $350,000.

3701
02:53:22.64 --> 02:53:27.04
But anyway, and he wouldn't debate me either.

3702
02:53:27.04 --> 02:53:31.08
He finally went to this silly thing on,

3703
02:53:31.08 --> 02:53:33.92
he was in DC because he couldn't quite return, which

3704
02:53:33.92 --> 02:53:35.08
is baloney.

3705
02:53:35.08 --> 02:53:38.76
He was from the county north of where we live.

3706
02:53:38.76 --> 02:53:44.08
But at any rate, it wasn't going to say that.

3707
02:53:44.08 --> 02:53:46.56
Well, it had to do with your racket that you're running,

3708
02:53:46.56 --> 02:53:48.92
your other racket.

3709
02:53:48.92 --> 02:53:52.64
Yeah, well, I was stockbroker at that point.

3710
02:53:52.64 --> 02:53:56.76
Because when I had my subdural hematoma,

3711
02:53:56.76 --> 02:54:00.88
they cut a hole in your head to take a piece out of your head.

3712
02:54:00.88 --> 02:54:02.92
Because it slept and fought about that.

3713
02:54:02.92 --> 02:54:06.88
But when I caught in there, you're John Glenn.

3714
02:54:06.88 --> 02:54:09.32
John Glenn fully recovered and so have I.

3715
02:54:09.32 --> 02:54:11.16
But a lot of people don't.

3716
02:54:11.16 --> 02:54:17.04
I think too, it's a matter of wanting to and deciding

3717
02:54:17.04 --> 02:54:18.88
to recover.

3718
02:54:18.88 --> 02:54:21.48
Because with my case, my right side,

3719
02:54:21.48 --> 02:54:22.52
it was on my left side.

3720
02:54:22.52 --> 02:54:25.16
And it's true, your left side didn't work right.

3721
02:54:25.16 --> 02:54:29.28
And it worked a little bit, but not real well.

3722
02:54:29.28 --> 02:54:33.20
And I couldn't walk right and stuff like that.

3723
02:54:33.20 --> 02:54:40.48
Anyway, so at any rate, how'd you get the registrar?

3724
02:54:40.48 --> 02:54:44.68
I am the Pennsylvania registrar for births and deaths

3725
02:54:44.68 --> 02:54:49.52
in only townships, 06 townships, and for several surrounding

3726
02:54:49.52 --> 02:54:50.64
townships.

3727
02:54:50.64 --> 02:54:52.36
If you die, you need a will.

3728
02:54:52.36 --> 02:54:57.000
And to have a will, you need an executor who distributes.

3729
02:54:57.000 --> 02:54:58.36
But you have to prove it.

3730
02:54:58.36 --> 02:54:59.32
Have somebody prove it.

3731
02:54:59.32 --> 02:55:03.80
This guy is dead, not just gone to South America, and so forth.

3732
02:55:03.80 --> 02:55:10.44
So you make certified copies of his death certificate,

3733
02:55:10.44 --> 02:55:14.48
issued generally by the hospital or the corner.

3734
02:55:14.48 --> 02:55:20.24
And that way, your executor, or man or woman's executor,

3735
02:55:20.24 --> 02:55:25.16
can probate the will and so forth and all that.

3736
02:55:25.16 --> 02:55:29.04
So at any rate, a year after, maybe 10 months

3737
02:55:29.04 --> 02:55:33.44
after I lost the election, I get to talk

3738
02:55:33.44 --> 02:55:37.16
to a guy named Bob Asher, who was a little bit of a character

3739
02:55:37.16 --> 02:55:39.52
and well-known in Pennsylvania politics,

3740
02:55:39.52 --> 02:55:42.72
because he took the heat and went to jail for something

3741
02:55:42.72 --> 02:55:48.12
he didn't do, but probably to protect a Pennsylvania senator

3742
02:55:48.12 --> 02:55:50.52
or maybe one of the governors, I don't know.

3743
02:55:50.52 --> 02:55:51.92
But he took the heat and everybody

3744
02:55:51.92 --> 02:55:54.04
agrees that Bob never did anything.

3745
02:55:54.04 --> 02:55:56.76
But he owns a candy company called Asher Candies.

3746
02:55:56.76 --> 02:56:00.72
It's well-known chocolates in Eastern Pennsylvania.

3747
02:56:00.72 --> 02:56:02.56
And there he was at this affair.

3748
02:56:02.56 --> 02:56:05.44
So I went up to him and I said, Bob, you owe me one.

3749
02:56:05.44 --> 02:56:07.08
He said, get out of here.

3750
02:56:07.08 --> 02:56:08.24
I said, you know who I am?

3751
02:56:08.24 --> 02:56:10.80
Oh, I know who you are.

3752
02:56:10.80 --> 02:56:13.88
I said, I rang 10,000 doorbells.

3753
02:56:13.88 --> 02:56:15.96
Yeah, I heard about that.

3754
02:56:15.96 --> 02:56:22.24
I said, he had to spend $350,000 to beat me.

3755
02:56:22.24 --> 02:56:23.88
Yeah.

3756
02:56:23.88 --> 02:56:26.20
Bob, we both know what that means.

3757
02:56:26.20 --> 02:56:29.84
He would have spent $35,000 against the guy in Fayette

3758
02:56:29.84 --> 02:56:34.36
County, he would have spent $58,000 at the guy in Pittsburgh,

3759
02:56:34.36 --> 02:56:40.44
he would have spent $102,000 in the guy in the Harrisburg race.

3760
02:56:40.44 --> 02:56:43.60
He spent it all to beat me.

3761
02:56:43.60 --> 02:56:45.12
Yeah, so what?

3762
02:56:45.12 --> 02:56:48.000
Bob, you owe me one.

3763
02:56:48.000 --> 02:56:51.44
A week later, the local guy that I knew very well

3764
02:56:51.44 --> 02:56:55.88
was a whole political office called me up and he said,

3765
02:56:55.88 --> 02:56:58.80
how'd you like to be a register of will?

3766
02:56:58.80 --> 02:57:02.24
What in the hell is that?

3767
02:57:02.24 --> 02:57:04.68
So I said, yeah, that's right.

3768
02:57:04.68 --> 02:57:06.04
How much does it pay?

3769
02:57:06.04 --> 02:57:08.08
Well, you won't make much.

3770
02:57:08.08 --> 02:57:10.12
You can make $35,000 doing it.

3771
02:57:10.12 --> 02:57:12.44
You can.

3772
02:57:12.44 --> 02:57:15.64
At any rate, they're trying to get rid of the Pennsylvania

3773
02:57:15.64 --> 02:57:16.16
Register.

3774
02:57:16.16 --> 02:57:19.88
Now I'm just sticking on because I figured right down

3775
02:57:19.88 --> 02:57:24.08
to the last day, so at any rate, that's how that happened.

3776
02:57:24.08 --> 02:57:28.64
So I was a stockbroker and if you start late in life

3777
02:57:28.64 --> 02:57:31.40
to be a stockbroker, you don't have much of an account.

3778
02:57:31.40 --> 02:57:35.08
And stuff, and I got to be a certain age

3779
02:57:35.08 --> 02:57:37.60
and I said to my wife, this is not cutting.

3780
02:57:37.60 --> 02:57:38.80
I got to do something else.

3781
02:57:38.80 --> 02:57:42.48
And right after that, my sister-in-law came to me

3782
02:57:42.48 --> 02:57:44.32
and she was German national.

3783
02:57:44.32 --> 02:57:45.04
You wouldn't know it.

3784
02:57:45.04 --> 02:57:46.60
She has zero accent.

3785
02:57:46.60 --> 02:57:51.28
She said, you sell bread that's good enough to sell in Germany.

3786
02:57:51.28 --> 02:57:53.000
You need to do this.

3787
02:57:53.000 --> 02:57:54.52
I'm still doing it by hand.

3788
02:57:54.52 --> 02:57:56.64
And one thing led to another there.

3789
02:57:56.64 --> 02:57:57.88
So that's what I do now.

3790
02:57:57.88 --> 02:58:01.24
And I'll tell you what, keep shit in shape.

3791
02:58:01.24 --> 02:58:04.76
You're not going to get fat doing this unless you want to.

3792
02:58:04.76 --> 02:58:07.72
I suppose you got to make sure you don't get too much of your own product, though.

3793
02:58:07.72 --> 02:58:08.60
That's true.

3794
02:58:08.60 --> 02:58:10.08
Just like the drug dealers.

3795
02:58:10.08 --> 02:58:11.12
No, no, no.

3796
02:58:11.12 --> 02:58:14.20
I say to people, people in the store say, I don't eat much bread.

3797
02:58:14.20 --> 02:58:16.000
I say, it's not the bread.

3798
02:58:16.000 --> 02:58:18.20
It's what you put on it.

3799
02:58:18.20 --> 02:58:21.68
Too much mayonnaise or too much strawberry jam

3800
02:58:21.68 --> 02:58:25.84
is what you do with it, not the stuff.

3801
02:58:25.84 --> 02:58:29.52
Well, what's the name, so where can people get your bread?

3802
02:58:29.52 --> 02:58:30.60
You got a shipment.

3803
02:58:30.60 --> 02:58:31.16
Oh, I got to.

3804
02:58:31.16 --> 02:58:35.32
